docs.abstract: The producers of the Fox drama announced that the actor, who was arrested on Thursday, would be removed from the final two episodes of the fifth season.
docs.snippet: The producers of the Fox drama announced that the actor, who was arrested on Thursday, would be removed from the final two episodes of the fifth season.
docs.lead_paragraph: The producers of the Fox drama “Empire” announced Friday that Jussie Smollett’s character would not appear in the final two episodes of the show’s fifth season. The announcement came a day after Chicago police arrested him and said he staged an attack against himself in a bid for publicity.

headline.main: Jussie Smollett Won’t Be on Final Episodes of ‘Empire’ Season
headline.print_headline: Smollett to Be Removed From Episodes of ‘Empire’

docs.abstract: A huge write-down, disappointing results and a regulatory inquiry pose big challenges for the owner of the Jell-O and Oscar Mayer brands.
docs.snippet: A huge write-down, disappointing results and a regulatory inquiry pose big challenges for the owner of the Jell-O and Oscar Mayer brands.
docs.lead_paragraph: Kraft Heinz, the food giant whose products include Jell-O and Oscar Mayer meats, on Thursday released a surprising batch of bad news that included a multibillion dollar write-down signaling a plunge in the value of some of its most famous brands.

headline.main: Kraft Heinz Stock Plunges as Tastes Change and S.E.C. Investigation Begins
headline.print_headline: Kraft Heinz Reveals S.E.C. Accounting Inquiry

docs.abstract: Critics of the film say it oversimplifies race relations. Its best-picture win complicated a night when the academy honored a diverse set of winners.
docs.snippet: Critics of the film say it oversimplifies race relations. Its best-picture win complicated a night when the academy honored a diverse set of winners.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Something seismic was happening during the Academy Awards ceremony on Sunday night. The Hollywood establishment, excoriated for its longtime exclusion of women and minorities, recognized African-American production design and costume virtuosos for the first time. Asian-American filmmakers were honored. A movie about a gay rock star collected four trophies.

headline.main: In ‘Green Book’ Victory, Oscar Critics See an Old Hollywood Tale
headline.print_headline: Diversity Ruled at the Oscars.  Then Came a Final Plot Twist.

docs.abstract: Liquid natural gas producers from Qatar, Norway and the U.S. are in line to deliver enough fuel to keep the lights on in Poland — and to complicate relations between Russia and the U.S.
docs.snippet: Liquid natural gas producers from Qatar, Norway and the U.S. are in line to deliver enough fuel to keep the lights on in Poland — and to complicate relations between Russia and the U.S.
docs.lead_paragraph: SWINOUJSCIE, Poland — Gargantuan tankers pull into this port on the Baltic Sea twice a month, ferrying liquid natural gas from producers in Qatar, Norway and, increasingly, the United States. The fuel will help light and heat millions of Polish homes, while gradually cutting the country’s dependence on coal.

headline.main: Burned by Russia, Poland Turns to U.S. for Natural Gas and Energy Security
headline.print_headline: How Chilled Gas Is Easing An Icy Energy Chokehold

docs.abstract: The agency found many users of the app, now known as TikTok, were under 13 and revealed sensitive personal information without their parents’ permission.
docs.snippet: The agency found many users of the app, now known as TikTok, were under 13 and revealed sensitive personal information without their parents’ permission.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Trade Commission on Wednesday announced a $5.7 million settlement with Musical.ly, a popular video social network now known as TikTok, over accusations that the company’s app illegally collected personal information about children.

headline.main: F.T.C. Hits Musical.ly With Record Fine for Child Privacy Violation
headline.print_headline: Network for Children Fined for Data Haul

docs.abstract: The departure of the “Game of Thrones”-era chief executive, Richard Plepler, comes after AT&T acquired Time Warner, the network’s former corporate home.
docs.snippet: The departure of the “Game of Thrones”-era chief executive, Richard Plepler, comes after AT&T acquired Time Warner, the network’s former corporate home.
docs.lead_paragraph: Richard Plepler, the gregarious chief executive of HBO and one of the most influential executives in entertainment, abruptly stepped down on Thursday. His decision came eight months after AT&T acquired Time Warner, the network’s corporate home, in an $85.4 billion deal.

headline.main: HBO’s C.E.O., an Emmy Magnet, Steps Down
headline.print_headline: HBO Chief, A Magnet For Emmys, Steps Down

byline.original: By John Koblin and Edmund Lee

docs.abstract: The ride-sharing company unveiled the prospectus for its initial public offering. It leads a wave of well-known tech start-ups that plan to go public this year.
docs.snippet: The ride-sharing company unveiled the prospectus for its initial public offering. It leads a wave of well-known tech start-ups that plan to go public this year.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Lyft pulled back the curtain on its business for the first time on Friday as it prepared to go public, officially starting the countdown on a horde of technology offerings that are set to bring new wealth to Silicon Valley this year.

headline.main: Lyft’s I.P.O. Filing Reveals Nearly $1 Billion in Losses
headline.print_headline: I.P.O. Filing By Lyft Bares Wider Losses
